The Delta South Leaders and Stakeholders Forum has congratulated the Speaker of the Delta State House of Assembly, Rt Hon Sheriff Oborevwori on his emergence as Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Governorship candidate for the 2023 general elections in the state. Oborevwori polled 590 votes to defeat his major contender and former Chief of Staff to the Governor, Chief David Edevbie who scored 113 votes. In a statement by the Forum’s Chairman, Chief Mike Loyibo lauded party delegates and stakeholders for their choice of Oborevwori whom he described as a complete Deltan. -Advertisement- He noted that Oborevwori had endeared himself to the people of the state with his unparalleled humility, friendship and outstanding service to the state. The Forum congratulated Governor Ifeanyi Okowa and the state Chairman of the party Chief Kingsley Esiso for ensuring a free, fair and credible primaries across the state. “Let me on behalf of members of the Delta South Leaders and Stakeholders Forum congratulate Mr Speaker, Rt. Hon Sheriff Oborevwori on his election as Delta PDP candidate for the 2023 governorship election in the state. “Today’s victory is a confirmation of the true resolve of the people to vote their preferred candidate and I must thank delegates and party leaders for their acceptance of Oborevwori across the state. “We urge fellow contestants to accept defeat in good faith and work together with our candidate to deliver the party in the 2023 general elections.” Loyibo admonished.